Fast, kind and decently priced. I do recommend it and will likely be back soon. The half a dozen yakitori it’s a must.
Food didn't taste good.
Amazing place

The food is amazing here, every week I go the food is always fresh. The two girls that work at the front on the weekends are so nice. But during the week the male workers at the front are really rude and give off bad vibes. Other than that this place is great. And I loveee the one piece Vibe

(Translated by Google) Great establishment, good service. Extraordinary atmosphere. By mistake I made an order with pork content and then they immediately changed it for beef. I recommend this place to visit.  (Original) Отличное заведение, хороший сервис. Неординарная атмосфера. По ошибке сделал заказ с содержанием свинины после чего мне тут же поменяли его на говядину. I like the sushi pancake 😂
Bad quality and portions, also messed up my order.

Just ordered and couldn't wait to make this review. The tonkotsu broth, chashu and the soy egg in the ramen...everything was perfect. The gyoza is amazing and tender. Also they have Melon Creamy Soda so that is already a win. This place is awesome! Recommended!
(Translated by Google) Very nice staff and delicious ramen  (Original) Очень хороший персонал и вкусный рамён

honestly this place is sooooo good! imo the best japanese place on 86th around the area and that says a lot. great service, great menu, their sushi is top tier compare to nearby places and the skewers, udon, and ramen are delicious as well. presentation is nice, was surprised some things actually look quite fancy!. wish i lived closer i would go much more often!!:) and it's super cool inside as well!!! 10/10
(Translated by Google) very delicious!  (Original) 超好吃！

I've been hooked since the very time time I stumbled upon this restaurant. I was taking a walk down 86 Street and decided to check it out. My daughter and I ordered a beef teriyaki bento box, a few skewers, and a kani salad. Everything was delicious. The manager even gave my daughter a Mango creamy soda, on the house! Our check came out to only around $25. On our way out the door, the staff gave my daughter a cute little comic-based key-chain as a souvenir. Now she wants to go back all the time!

This is my new favorite sushi spot! I found them on grubhub but their special sushi doesn't have descriptions (which is a touch annoying!) so I jumped on google. Unfortunately their menu still doesn't have their special sushi descriptions BUT I found my favorite anime characters in the drink section and then on their walls! I love One Piece so I convinced my roommate to check it out. We ordered for pick up. It was ready when we got there and contactless pick up was a bit awkward but easy enough. The restaurant has a big One Piece mural on the outside so it was worth the trip! I can't wait to dine in [eventually 🤞🏻]. The food was good! Coconut shrimp and all of the sushi rolls we had were delicious! We guessed on two specials and were pleased (We googled roll names and hoped for the best!) I will definitely be ordering again to check out the ramen and everything else on the menu!
All the food taste gooood~

The signature tofu and eggplant is a great vegetarian food.  The sauce seems like it is from sweet and spicy bottle sauce but the way it is fried is what makes it good.  The batter is tempura batter.  Litely batter and fried.
Very good food, cozy atmosphere, great service. We will be back.
So good it is so cute how the restaurant is anime themed if u go u must try the pork belly!!!!!!!!!
Pretty cool One Piece themed restaurant!

I had chicken cutlet, tofu curry noodles and some BBQ skewers for dinner. For 9 dollars I got a very thin sliced of chicken cutlet, the size is just like an appetizer.  The BBQ skewers are hard and salty. My bf love the curry but it is too sweet for me.
Best place to eat and relax!!!
Nice place
This place feels really warm and welcoming and  the prices are really good for what you're getting
Low cost fusion Japanese food. Lunch special everyday with 9 diff types of sushi and sashimi. One piece theme and clean environment. Rare gems among the Chinese restaurants area.

SUUUUUUPER place. Decked out in one piece memorabilia like wanted posters, figurines, and wallpapers. A definite must visit if your a one piece fan. The foods pretty affordable and it has what you would expect at a Japanese restaurant.

This Asian Fusion spot has some amazing food. I come here often and have never left dissatisfied. Sushi is always fresh and on point. Probably some of the best sushi around south Brooklyn. I highly recommend this place, especially for late night eats.
Nope, never again. Made me sick.

First time going here. It was an experience. The decor, and atmosphere is really great, it makes you want to read the manga, or watch the anime all over again. However, I wish the dishes were more dedicated to the anime, otherwise it seems like a very basic menu, where I could get these food items at any other Chinese restaurant. It was a nice thing to try out for a Christmas dinner, but not completely impressed.
Nice
Delicious.  Good service.
Cool place to go

Nice asian fusion restaurant where u can get korean, Japanese or thai style dishes. I originally came mainly because of the one piece decor but I was quite satisfied with the food too. I ordered this thai dish called Gaeng Phao, which is a vegetable dish with spicy coconut sauce and grilled chicken on top. I liked how it was quite flavorful and not only msg flavoring. On the other hand, the seating was quite comfortable and spacious.
Awesome meal as always
Nobody picks up the phone
Good food 👍
The food was delicious and the one piece decor was cute.

My family and I are regulars here. The food tastes great! It's clean there, the atmosphere is very fun, and the service is beyond awesome! I've brought many friends and family here to eat and they all enjoyed it! I definitely recommend Kushi to you all as well!!!
Food were all so well seasoned in my opinion  and very friendly and accommodating staff. Will definitely come back to try other dishes 😋
Love this place, delicious food and nice service
Great service with good taste in Japanese Cuisine

(Translated by Google) One Piece theme restaurant, very comfortable!  (Original) 海贼王主题餐厅，挺舒服的！
Beautiful atmosphere and the food was great

Amazing place , great One Piece themed restaurant for those who love anime.  The service was really amazing , always checked on us and frequently visited us for tea.  The food was amazing , and the options were huge variety! will be coming back!
Fusian delicious amazing!

The food was good, my family went for the lunch specials, bento boxes and thai dishes.  The bento boxes we had were pork katsu and chicken teriyaki, they were yummy.  We also had penang curry and pad thai.  These were good, better than average. The ambiance is nice, with One Piece themed art and collectables.  We are definitely coming back to try the ramen.
The food was excellent. Really cool atmosphere, and the service was very nice as well.
Amazing food, amazing service hands down
I had ramen which was alright not the best service was ok
Excellent customer attention!!!
Go for their lunch special. Good price and the food is good!
(Translated by Google) MAMADE  (Original) MAMADE

The overall taste of the ramyun is good. There is a good balance of toppings which includes corn, onion, seaweed, bamboo shoots, two alices of naruto, one soy sauce egg, and two braised pork slices. Their fried oyster is good. I just wished they didn't use so much better to fry. Its thick compared to the smaller oyster in the middle and it makes the whole thing unbalanced.

This place is a phenomenal little gem in Brooklyn. The ramen, pork katsu and curry tasted so authentic and very good. But the pork was a bit too fatty, and the curry was a little bit too liquidy. Taste trumped all though. mmediately came back the next week for more. Highly suggest this place, and the prices are fair too

Don't listen to the other reviews, the customer service was spectacular, and the food was really good :)  [[See Pictures For Reference:]] The ladies serving my friend and I were extremely nice. They kept pouring us tea and took away plates when we were done. Our table was never a mess.  NOW LET'S GET TO THE FOOD! The pork ramen was better than expected! They gave us double the food than a normal restaurant does! Double the egg, double the pork, double the fish cakes. Also, the broth was very savory.  The salmon hand roll was also very delicious, the fish was fresh.  The beef tongue and chicken gizzard skewers were very good.  The fried oysters AND the saury fish were one of the most delicious! It was very very tasty!  Not included in the picture were garlic chicken wings. Those were very good, crispy on the outside, and juicy on the inside.  This place was amazing, will definitely come again.

Looove this place! The Takoyaki is generous with several pieces of octopus in it. The yakitori and fried chicken wings are perfect snacks when you don't want a big meal (or perhaps something in-between meals). All the fried rice has the proper "wok hey Mei" which we love and know that a skilled chef works here. It's awesome they seamless too! I hope they never change their amaaaazing chefs.
For those who love Anime - One Piece themed restaurant. Walls, posters, figurines, etc.  Love, love, love the menu and prices. The sushi was fresh and sooooo goood.  Nice atmosphere.
Delicious. Grilled scallop with cheese and crab was good; however, I do wish the crab was actual crab. Great portions. I would go again. 🤷‍♀️
Excellent Asian Fusion! I had the spicy wontons and the Phad King ( see photos). Courteous, prompt service and perfect portions!
Miso ramen tasty big bowl. Love the mixed tempura.. Crunchy but not greasy. Great service. Our tea cups and water cup was always filled. We will be back again to enjoy

I work nearby and it’s by far the best place to grab a quick and outstanding lunch. They fry food better than anyone. Sushi is amazing too. Haven’t tried the ramen, but I would be shocked if that wasn’t also delicious. $3.50 for a bottle of Kirin is such a steal too.

Great place for casual Japanese food. The menu has much more variety compared to other sushi restaurants around the area. I especially recommend the grilled eggplant and port katsu rice. The interior is decorated with one piece art which I loved as a one piece fan.

Good food with decent price and fun interior. I ordered the grilled sushi set and ikura. While the pieces in the sushi set look small they are flavorful and actually quite filling. I thought I may need to order more but in the end I didn't have too. The slightly grilled sushi were not fully cooked so they still have that 'melt-in-mouth' impacts. They gave a bit of everything too, like tuna, shrimp, squid, saba, salmon, red clam, avocado (surprisingly good!), etc. Taste fresh too! The music is more underground type, which is more suitable for young ppl to come hangout with friends. If you are seeking the quiet Japanese feel, this place is probably not for you (well but you could expect that from the One Piece theme interior). Overall a nice place for the bucks.
Amazing sushi. Very nice udon.

The theme of this location is one piece can it be any better? Of course the food is delicious amd the prices are fair. Definitely recommend this place to anyone that loves one piece or food. Will for sure come back!
Good ramen near Coney Island is rare.
Was great! Quick service, has one piece anime decor as well! I ordered some sushi,sesame pancake, okonomiyaki and takoyaki. It was delicious! I recommend to people who want good Japanese food!
So so
Food is okay, not great. Service was sub par. It's not actually an izakaya either, at least not yet.
Service is amazing, food was fast (10 mins) and delicious. Very filling and affordable.
Had most of the appetizers and yakitori with drinks, the food was delicious and the service was good, couldn't have asked for more, will definitely be back.
Sushi is fresh,fish is delicious.Sesame cake is no taste…ordinary。
this place got really nice decorations and if you’re an One Piece fan, you should definitely come here,ordered pork ramen.
A cozy Izakaya with authentic Japanese flavors decorated/served in  traditional dishware, have been there 3 times already, and plan to concur all the dishes!

I ordered the Atka Mackeral and Pork Ramen. One thing I can say is this place is not for Ramen. The "tonkotsu" broth is flavorless.  The topping tastes good, just like regular ramen topping. The chashu is little chewy, it doesn't really melt in your mouth. However, it tastes good overall. The Atka Mackeral tastes little salty.  In my overall experience, I would give it 3 stars, but before I left. The staff said, "if it is not good, we will make it again." To me, it is a very good attitude toward their food and customers. Hence, I give it 4 stars.

I noticed this place recently opened and I love trying new restaurants so I dropped by here for lunch. Overall, the food was mediocre and a little too salty for my palette. I ordered a chicken teriyaki lunch bento and a pork ramen. The chasiu for the pork ramen was much too fatty and the ramen noodles felt a little undercooked. I wouldn't recommend it unless you had a severe ramen craving that had to be satisfied. The chicken teriyaki bento was alright but for $9.50 I think I could get more and better at other Japanese restaurants in the area. However, on the plus side, the decor was nice and the service was okay.
Great place! Food was delicious, ambiance is fun and staff was attentive. Will definitely be going back!
